				Is he my darling child?
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				For as often as I speak against him,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				I do remember him still.
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="v" cid="c24031020.3">
				</crossref>
				Therefore my heart
				<note nid="n24031020.1">
				</note>
				 yearns for him;
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				I will surely have mercy on him,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="declares">
				</begin-line>
				declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				.
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031021">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="21">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="w" cid="c24031021.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Set up road markers for yourself;
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				make yourself guideposts;
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="x" cid="c24031021.2">
				</crossref>
				consider well the highway,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="w" cid="c24031021.3">
				</crossref>
				the road by which you went.
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				Return, O virgin Israel,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				return to these your cities.
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031022">
			</marker>
			<verse num="22">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="y" cid="c24031022.1">
				</crossref>
				How long will you waver,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="z" cid="c24031022.2">
				</crossref>
				O faithless daughter?
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				For the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				 has created a new thing on the earth:
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				a woman encircles a man.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<end-block-indent
				>
			</end-block-indent>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031023">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="23">
				Thus says the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				 of hosts, the God of Israel: 
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Once more they shall use these words in the land of Judah and in its cities, 
				<crossref let="a" cid="c24031023.1">
				</crossref>
				when I restore their fortunes:

				<end-paragraph
					>
				</end-paragraph>
				<begin-block-indent
					>
				</begin-block-indent>
				<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
				</begin-paragraph>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="b" cid="c24031023.2">
				</crossref>
				<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				The 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				 bless you, 
				<crossref let="c" cid="c24031023.3">
				</crossref>
				O habitation of righteousness,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="d" cid="c24031023.4">
				</crossref>
				O holy hill!
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<end-block-indent
				>
			</end-block-indent>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031024">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph class="same-paragraph">
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="24">
				<crossref let="e" cid="c24031024.1">
				</crossref>
				And Judah and all its cities shall dwell there together, and 
				<crossref let="e" cid="c24031024.2">
				</crossref>
				the farmers and those who wander with their flocks.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031025">
			</marker>
			<verse num="25">
				For I will 
				<crossref let="f" cid="c24031025.1">
				</crossref>
				satisfy the weary soul, and every languishing soul I will replenish.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031026">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="26">
				At this I awoke and looked, and my sleep was pleasant to me.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031027">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="27">
				<crossref let="g" cid="c24031027.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Behold, the days are coming, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				, when 
				<crossref let="h" cid="c24031027.2">
				</crossref>
				I will sow the house of Israel and the house of Judah with 
				<crossref let="i" cid="c24031027.3">
				</crossref>
				the seed of man and the seed of beast.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031028">
			</marker>
			<verse num="28">
				And it shall come to pass that 
				<crossref let="j" cid="c24031028.1">
				</crossref>
				as I have watched over them 
				<crossref let="k" cid="c24031028.2">
				</crossref>
				to pluck up and break down, to overthrow, destroy, and bring harm, 
				<crossref let="j" cid="c24031028.3">
				</crossref>
				so I will watch over them 
				<crossref let="l" cid="c24031028.4">
				</crossref>
				to build and to plant, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031029">
			</marker>
			<verse num="29">
				In those days they shall no longer say:

				<end-paragraph
					>
				</end-paragraph>
				<begin-block-indent
					>
				</begin-block-indent>
				<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
				</begin-paragraph>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="m" cid="c24031029.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				The fathers have eaten sour grapes,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				and the children's teeth are set on edge.
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<end-block-indent
				>
			</end-block-indent>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031030">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph class="same-paragraph">
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="30">
				<crossref let="n" cid="c24031030.1">
				</crossref>
				But everyone shall die for his own sin. Each man who eats sour grapes, his teeth shall be set on edge.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031031">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				The New Covenant
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="31">
				<crossref let="o" cid="c24031031.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Behold, the days are coming, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				, when I will make 
				<crossref let="p" cid="c24031031.2">
				</crossref>
				a new covenant with the house of Israel and the house of Judah,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031032">
			</marker>
			<verse num="32">
				not like the covenant that I made with their fathers on the day when 
				<crossref let="q" cid="c24031032.1">
				</crossref>
				I took them by the hand to bring them out of the land of Egypt, my covenant that they broke, 
				<crossref let="r" cid="c24031032.2">
				</crossref>
				though I was their husband, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031033">
			</marker>
			<verse num="33">
				<crossref let="s" cid="c24031033.1">
				</crossref>
				But this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				: 
				<crossref let="s" cid="c24031033.2">
				</crossref>
				I will put my law within them, and I will write it 
				<crossref let="t" cid="c24031033.3">
				</crossref>
				on their hearts. 
				<crossref let="u" cid="c24031033.4">
				</crossref>
				And I will be their God, and they shall be my people.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031034">
			</marker>
			<verse num="34">
				And no longer shall each one teach his neighbor and each his brother, saying, 
				<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Know the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				,
				<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<crossref let="v" cid="c24031034.1">
				</crossref>
				for they shall all know me, 
				<crossref let="w" cid="c24031034.2">
				</crossref>
				from the least of them to the greatest, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				. For 
				<crossref let="x" cid="c24031034.3">
				</crossref>
				I will forgive their iniquity, and 
				<crossref let="y" cid="c24031034.4">
				</crossref>
				I will remember their sin no more.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031035">
			</marker>
			<begin-block-indent
				>
			</begin-block-indent>
			<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="35">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				Thus says the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				who 
				<crossref let="z" cid="c24031035.1">
				</crossref>
				gives the sun for light by day
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				and 
				<crossref let="a" cid="c24031035.2">
				</crossref>
				the fixed order of the moon and the stars for light by night,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				who stirs up the sea so that its waves roarù
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="b" cid="c24031035.3">
				</crossref>
				the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				 of hosts is his name:
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031036">
			</marker>
			<verse num="36">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="c" cid="c24031036.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				If this fixed order departs
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				from before me, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				then shall the offspring of Israel cease
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				from being a nation before me forever.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031037">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph class="line-group">
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="37">
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				Thus says the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				:
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				If the heavens above can be measured,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				and the foundations of the earth below can be explored,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line
					>
				</begin-line>
				<crossref let="d" cid="c24031037.1">
				</crossref>
				then I will cast off all the offspring of Israel
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="indent">
				</begin-line>
				for all that they have done,
				<end-line class="br">
				</end-line>
				<begin-line class="declares">
				</begin-line>
				declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				<end-line
					>
				</end-line>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<end-block-indent
				>
			</end-block-indent>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031038">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="38">
				<crossref let="e" cid="c24031038.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Behold, the days are coming, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				, when the city shall be rebuilt for the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				<crossref let="f" cid="c24031038.2">
				</crossref>
				from the Tower of Hananel to 
				<crossref let="g" cid="c24031038.3">
				</crossref>
				the Corner Gate.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031039">
			</marker>
			<verse num="39">
				<crossref let="h" cid="c24031039.1">
				</crossref>
				And the measuring line shall go out farther, straight to the hill Gareb, and shall then turn to Goah.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24031040">
			</marker>
			<verse num="40">
				<crossref let="i" cid="c24031040.1">
				</crossref>
				The whole valley of the dead bodies and the ashes, and all the fields as far as the 
				<crossref let="j" cid="c24031040.2">
				</crossref>
				brook Kidron, to the corner of 
				<crossref let="k" cid="c24031040.3">
				</crossref>
				the Horse Gate toward the east, 
				<crossref let="l" cid="c24031040.4">
				</crossref>
				shall be sacred to the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				. 
				<crossref let="m" cid="c24031040.5">
				</crossref>
				It shall not be uprooted or overthrown anymore forever.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
		</chapter>
	</book>
